{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cb84fca5-639c-4ffd-b6b7-1e91b46fd203","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\n**Tools for analyzing .NET crash dumps:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside the REPL:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **`lldb` with SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg/Visual Studio** (Windows) — open the `.dmp` directly.\n\n**Quick triage steps:**\n1. Run `dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp`\n2. Use `pe` to print the exception that caused the crash\n3. Use `clrstack` to see the call stack\n4. Use `threads` then `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` to inspect other threads\n\nWould you like me to walk you through running any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ec383830-2c13-436b-a6f7-e95d0f77657a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for \"Configure and collect crash dumps\" and explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\".\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":446,"requestId":"608D:35D604:318BE6:40349F:69FFE5B7"},"id":"de801074-4920-483a-a148-3d991431f218","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:56:18.165Z","parentId":"2077918d-3278-42c3-a3aa-842aba9e2e49"}
